                                 //  If a equals b, c is zero. Else c is some other value

    c[0] | c[1] ... | c[n] = d   // OR the bits
                                 //  If c equals zero, d equals zero. Else d equals 1

Note: `a,b,c` are n-bit integers and `d` is a bit

